On Sun, 2026-01-25 at 10:18 +1100, NeilBrown wrote:
>=20
> For v3 we cannot know the client because a client might have multiple IP
> addresses.
>=20
> For v4 we could use the clientid as you say but I suspect inter-server
> copies might hit problems as the client passes its filehandle to one
> server and it passes it on the another.  However do the client pass on a
> clientid as well??  In that case we might be able to make it work.
>=20
>=20

I don't think it passes a clientid (and certainly not the long form,
which you'd need to use). You do get a destination stateid though,
which you could use to infer the long-form clientid. It would be
necessary for the client to use the same clientid string for all
servers if we did this (but I think that's the case for most).

Thinking about this some more, I think the better way to do this would
probably be to tie it to TLS, so that you factor in the client's
certificate. That would work on either v3 or v4.

Inter-server copies would still be a problem, but you could probably
make it work between trusted servers by giving them the same key, or by
using a side-band protocol.
--=20
